node.text: If you don’t heal what hurt you, you’ll  bleed on people that didn’t cut you. @thefemalewarhol
You start to realize it’s not where you go in this world... but who you go with that matters.
Love is not about finding the right person, but becoming the right person.

Our greatest matches will be simply be people who make us better. Someone who wants what best for you is what’s best for you:) They don’t even try... it’s just their presence or the way they live their life that makes us want to be better than we are today. We begin to change not because the other person controls us, but our admiration for them is all the incentive we need. When we admire our lovers, partners or friends it’s the purest driving force behind personal growth and change. So when you meet people who listen to you and make you smile and who laugh when you do those little quirky things, embrace them and don’t let go. You have found something special.

I think we live in a world where we don’t feel ourselves anymore. Instead we feel numb from all the social media, the technology. The increasing influence from all over the world is slowly killing our vibes. It silences our inner voice and doesn’t let us hear our true self. Constantly being told how to dress, how to act, where to go and how to look. We begin to become ashamed of ourselves and slip into daydreams that replace living. We begin to feel uncomfortable in our bodies and not enjoying ourselves because we want to fit in perfectly playing a role to be included into this society. Being different is not cool, it won’t get you enough likes:( It doesn’t satisfy the large mass and what they don’t understand, they hate.
Empathy is so rare these days and the ability to see everyone has their own struggles and that I don’t need to understand everyone’s every move... Why they paint their nails or don’t wear a bra or wear a bra, Why they are hanging out with that person or reading that book. I don’t have to understand because it’s not my fucking business. I have my own life to celebrate and I’m gonna focus on that.
We are all so much more than we show on the outside, our dreams our feelings... we were raised being told not to judge a book by its cover and it’s exactly what we are doing now. We all bleed the same blood, cherish the same deep love and cry the same hot salty tears when we are hurt. We all want to explore and save this beautiful planet while cherishing this gift we call life. Not becoming machines dressing the same, thinking the same locked into some brainwashing society full of fake happiness.  I know looking yourself in the eyes trying to find your own frequency is tough sometimes, really tough...you may lose friends, friends who you thought would always be there. You may even lose family who doesn’t understand you, but it’s so important you take these paths to learn and grow from them. Remember life is a journey and journeys aren’t always easy. There will storms and rain but it’s needed to wash away the dirt from your soul. Embrace the journey and do you to the fullest. Fall in love with becoming the best, most original version of yourself.

THE CAPACITY TO BE ALONE IS THE CAPACITY TO LOVE ❤️
It may seem paradoxical to you but it’s not. It’s the truth. Only those who are capable of being alone are capable of true love, of sharing and going into the deepest core of another person without possessing the other, without depending on the other and without becoming dependent on the other. They allow the other absolute freedom because they know if the other leaves, they will be as happy as they are now. Their happiness can not be taken by the other....as it is not given by the other.
